The mirror of `item-checked-without-completed-class.txtar`. The `<li>` carries
the `completed` class but the `.toggle` is unchecked, so this projects
`[ ] ~buy milk~` — strike marks, empty box. Again a real app would not render
this; the point is that the class and the checkbox are read independently.
Pins: `[x]` and `~…~` are independent outputs.

This fixture omits the footer to keep the case on the item line.

-- dom.html --
<section class="todoapp">
	<header class="header">
		<h1>todos</h1>
		<input class="new-todo" placeholder="What needs to be done?">
	</header>
	<section class="main">
		<input id="toggle-all" class="toggle-all" type="checkbox">
		<label for="toggle-all">Mark all as complete</label>
		<ul class="todo-list">
			<li class="completed" data-id="t1">
				<div class="view">
					<input class="toggle" type="checkbox">
					<label>buy milk</label>
					<button class="destroy"></button>
				</div>
				<input class="edit" value="buy milk">
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</section>

-- projection.txt --
v > ""
#t1 [ ] ~buy milk~
